  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Bar Council of Maharashtra and Goa versus Rajiv Nareshchandra Narula & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_9_1363_1377','2025INSC1147'); ><font size='4'> <strong>BAR COUNCIL OF MAHARASHTRA AND GOA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>RAJIV NARESHCHANDRA NARULA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 1363</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1147</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008892025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Matter pertains to filing of frivolous complaint against two advocates before the Bar Council which took cognizance of the complaint and referred the complaint to the Disciplinary Committee for inquiry. Headnotes&dagger; Advocates Act, 1961 &ndash; s.35 &ndash; Punishment &ndash; Complaint by one against an advocate alleging professional misconduct u/s.35, for his role in identifying the plaintiff in the consent terms of a civil suit &ndash; Judge-Advocate of the Bar Council took cognizance of the complaint and referred the complaint to the Disciplinary<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 24-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 12232/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_9_1363_1377','2025INSC1147','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'